article.headline: Virginia Tech 88, Miami 83
article.story: CORAL GABLES, Fla. -- Malcolm Delaney scored 29 points to lead Virginia Tech to an 88-83 overtime victory over Miami on Sunday. Delaney's 3-pointer with 1:49 left in overtime gave the Hokies (14-5, 4-1 Atlantic Coast Conference) the lead for good at 84-83. A.D. Vasallo also scored 28 points. Vasallo and Dorenzo Hudson each converted two free throws in the final 26 seconds to secure Virginia Tech's fifth-straight victory. Dwayne Collins scored 23 to lead Miami (14-5, 3-3). Collins' short field goal with 7:03 remaining put the Hurricanes ahead 63-57, but Virginia Tech answered with a 9-0 run, including a pair of 3s from Vassallo. Brian Asbury?s 3-pointer with 25 seconds remaining in regulation tied the game for Miami at 77-all. Delaney missed a possible game-winning jumper with 2 seconds left for Virginia Tech, sending the game into OT.
